      <section id="id45391727">
        <title>To determine the effect that evergreen and deciduous trees have on the organisms that live in and under them. [LO 1.2]</title>
        <list id="id45391738" list-type="bulleted">
          <item>The important thing is that the learners must think for themselves and venture answers, e.g.</item>
        </list>
        <list id="id45391748" list-type="bulleted">
          <item>birds can make nests in deciduous trees only during certain times of the year</item>
          <item>deciduous trees only provide food for insects at certain times of the year</item>
          <item>the soil under a deciduous tree might be drier and harder than under an evergreen tree</item>
          <item>an evergreen tree always provides shade for plants and animals that like shade, etc.</item>
        </list>
        <para id="id45391779">EVERYTHING THAT HAPPENS IN NATURE IS OF SIGNIFICANCE</para>
        <para id="id45391784">For example, look at the following two types of trees:</para>
